Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of multiple orange and yellow blocks
- It has two vertical orange cylindrical pillars
- Three orange triangular roof pieces on top
- Two yellow rectangular blocks forming a horizontal cross shape
- Total blocks used: 7 (2 vertical cylinders, 3 roof pieces, 2 yellow rectangles)
- The structure has multiple layers arranged vertically

Block identification from dictionary:
- Orange cylinders: Block #6 (vertical orientation)
- Yellow rectangles: Block #1 and #2 (horizontal orientations)
- Orange triangular roofs: Block #14 (appears three times)

Assembly order from bottom to top:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 6
    Step2: Move block with index 6
    Step3: Move block with index 1
    Step4: Move block with index 2
    Step5: Move block with index 14
    Step6: Move block with index 14
    Step7: Move block with index 14
}

This assembly sequence starts with the two vertical pillars, then adds the horizontal yellow blocks forming the cross shape, and finally places the three triangular roof pieces on top of the structure.
